        {
          "code": "implausible",
          "distractor_index": 1,
          "note": "'Making the seller expect the same rep to handle every later transaction step' has no causal connection to winging a call — no learner can construct a story where being unprepared produces this expectation. It is fabricated process trivia that does not answer the stem's question, the same non-engagement defect class this record was rejected for twice."
        },
        {
          "code": "implausible",
          "distractor_index": 2,
          "note": "'Shortening the follow-up schedule below the seller's decision timeline' is likewise a non-sequitur for the risk of being unprepared on a call; nothing in the lesson or common sense links winging it to follow-up cadence."
        },
        {
          "code": "style_mismatch",
          "distractor_index": null,
          "note": "Compounding giveaway: the key is the only option written in the lesson's own vocabulary (trust, preparation — echoed across ch02-002/003/049/050) while all three distractors use CRM-ops vocabulary (rep routing, follow-up schedule) that appears nowhere in this deck's backs, so the key is isolable by register alone."
        },
